<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Energy Basics</h1>
        <h2>Individual & Device Protection</h2>
        <p>Individuals are protected against electrocution and fire, while devices are protected against fire, power stability issues, and lightning effects.</p>
        
        <h2>Best Practices</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>All live cables must be inaccessible.</li>
            <li>The neutral and canopy of all generators must be grounded.</li>
            <li>All sockets must be grounded.</li>
            <li>There must be Residual Current Device (RCD) protection on all circuits.</li>
            <li>Miniature Circuit Breakers (MCB) and electrical wires must be properly scaled.</li>
            <li>ABC type fire extinguishers should be placed near distribution boards and generators.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Monitoring & Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>Facilities are inspected by an electrician 6 months after opening and every 18 months thereafter. Logs are responsible for energy assessments and service continuity.</p>
    </div>
